  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A use-of-funds statement is a breakdown of how a business intends to allocate capital received from investors or lenders. It specifies what percentage or dollar amount of the investment will go to each category of expenditure — equipment, inventory, [marketing](../../marketing/terms/marketing-plan.md), working capital, hiring, facility build-out, debt repayment, or other costs.",
